OL,3,CCoroner warns over viral trends after
OL,4,Cboy dies inhaling deodorant
OL,6,FA coroner has issued a warning about
OL,7,F"toxic" social media algorithms after
OL,8,Fa schoolboy died from inhaling
OL,9,Fdeodorant while copying a viral trend.
OL,11,FOliver Gorman, 12, was found
OL,12,Funresponsive in his bed with empty
OL,13,Faerosol cans scattered around him at
OL,14,Fhis home in Hyde, Tameside after
OL,15,Freturning from a family holiday.
OL,17,FHe was rushed to hospital but could
OL,18,Fnot be resuscitated.
OL,20,FThe dangerous trend is widespread on
OL,21,Fsocial media, "particularly TikTok".
